			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of the 21-year-old E.G. on economic sanctions and discrimination before the German occupation, ghettoization in
					Nagyszőllős/Vinohradov, the behavior of the non-Jewish population, the deportation to and selection in Birkenau, his experiences
					as a member of the commando “Kanada”, witnessing murder in the gas chambers, slave labor in Warsaw, and a death march at the end
					of the war to Dachau and later to Buchenwald, slave labor in a stone quarry near Lublin, in Gross Rosen, and a construction site
					in Mühldorf.</p>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
